#. <section class="sutta" id="sn3.25"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.25:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.25:0.2"
msgid "3. Tatiyavagga"
msgstr "3. Kosala"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 25. Pabbatūpamasutta → pabbatopamasuttaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn3.25:0.3"
msgid "25. Pabbatūpamasutta"
msgstr "25. The Simile of the Mountain"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.225"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.25:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn3.25:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "King Pasenadi of Kosala sat to one side, and the Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "sn3.25:1.3"
msgid "“handa kuto nu tvaṃ, mahārāja, āgacchasi divā divassā”ti?"
msgstr "“So, great king, where are you coming from in the middle of the day?”"

msgctxt "sn3.25:1.4"
msgid ""
"“Yāni tāni, bhante, raññaṃ khattiyānaṃ muddhāvasittānaṃ issariyamadamattānaṃ "
"kāmagedhapariyuṭṭhitānaṃ janapadatthāvariyappattānaṃ mahantaṃ "
"pathavimaṇḍalaṃ abhivijiya ajjhāvasantānaṃ rājakaraṇīyāni bhavanti, tesu "
"khvāhaṃ, etarahi ussukkamāpanno”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, there are anointed aristocratic kings who are infatuated with power, "
"and obsessed with greed for sensual pleasures. They have attained stability "
"in the country, occupying a vast conquered territory. Today I have been busy "
"fulfilling the duties of such kings.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.101"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.226"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.25:2.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, "
msgstr "“What do you think, great king? "

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.2"
msgid "idha te puriso āgaccheyya puratthimāya disāya saddhāyiko paccayiko."
msgstr "Suppose a trustworthy and reliable man were to come from the east."

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.3"
msgid "So taṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "He’d approach you and say:"

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.4"
msgid "‘yagghe, mahārāja, jāneyyāsi, ahaṃ āgacchāmi puratthimāya disāya."
msgstr "‘Please sir, you should know this. I come from the east."

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.5"
msgid ""
"Tatthaddasaṃ mahantaṃ pabbataṃ abbhasamaṃ, sabbe pāṇe nippothento āgacchati."
msgstr ""
"There I saw a huge mountain that reached the clouds. And it was coming this "
"way, crushing all creatures."

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.6"
msgid "Yaṃ te, mahārāja, karaṇīyaṃ, taṃ karohī’ti."
msgstr "So then, great king, do what you must!’"

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.7"
msgid "Atha dutiyo puriso āgaccheyya pacchimāya disāya … pe …"
msgstr "Then a second trustworthy and reliable man were to come from the west …"

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.8"
msgid "atha tatiyo puriso āgaccheyya uttarāya disāya …"
msgstr "a third from the north …"

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.9"
msgid "atha catuttho puriso āgaccheyya dakkhiṇāya disāya saddhāyiko paccayiko."
msgstr "and a fourth from the south."

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.10"
msgid "So taṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "He’d approach you and say:"

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.11"
msgid "‘yagghe, mahārāja, jāneyyāsi, ahaṃ āgacchāmi dakkhiṇāya disāya."
msgstr "‘Please sir, you should know this. I come from the south."

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.12"
msgid ""
"Tatthaddasaṃ mahantaṃ pabbataṃ abbhasamaṃ sabbe pāṇe nippothento āgacchati."
msgstr ""
"There I saw a huge mountain that reached the clouds. And it was coming this "
"way, crushing all creatures."

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.13"
msgid "Yaṃ te, mahārāja, karaṇīyaṃ taṃ karohī’ti."
msgstr "So then, great king, do what you must!’"

#. VAR: manussakkhaye → manussakāye (mr)
msgctxt "sn3.25:2.14"
msgid ""
"Evarūpe te, mahārāja, mahati mahabbhaye samuppanne dāruṇe manussakkhaye "
"dullabhe manussatte kimassa karaṇīyan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Should such a dire threat arise—a terrible loss of human life, when human "
"birth is so rare—what would you do?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.25:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Evarūpe me, bhante, mahati mahabbhaye samuppanne dāruṇe manussakkhaye "
"dullabhe manussatte kimassa karaṇīyaṃ aññatra dhammacariyāya aññatra "
"samacariyāya aññatra kusalakiriyāya aññatra puññakiriyāyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, what could I do but practice the teachings, practice morality, doing "
"skillful and good actions?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.102"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.227"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.25:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Ārocemi kho te, mahārāja, paṭivedemi kho te, mahārāja, adhivattati kho taṃ, "
"mahārāja, jarāmaraṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“I tell you, great king, I announce to you: old age and death are advancing "
"upon you."

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.2"
msgid "Adhivattamāne ce te, mahārāja, jarāmaraṇe kimassa karaṇīyan”ti?"
msgstr "Since old age and death are advancing upon you, what would you do?”"

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.3"
msgid ""
"“Adhivattamāne ca me, bhante, jarāmaraṇe kimassa karaṇīyaṃ aññatra "
"dhammacariyāya samacariyāya kusalakiriyāya puññakiriyāya?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, what can I do but practice the teachings, practice morality, doing "
"skillful and good actions?"

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.4"
msgid ""
"Yāni tāni, bhante, raññaṃ khattiyānaṃ muddhāvasittānaṃ issariyamadamattānaṃ "
"kāmagedhapariyuṭṭhitānaṃ janapadatthāvariyappattānaṃ mahantaṃ "
"pathavimaṇḍalaṃ abhivijiya ajjhāvasantānaṃ hatthiyuddhāni bhavanti;"
msgstr ""
"Sir, there are anointed aristocratic kings who are infatuated with power, "
"and obsessed with greed for sensual pleasures. They have attained stability "
"in the country, occupying a vast conquered territory. Such kings engage in "
"battles of elephants,"

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.5"
msgid ""
"tesampi, bhante, hatthiyuddhānaṃ natthi gati natthi visayo adhivattamāne "
"jarāmaraṇe."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.6"
msgid "Yānipi tāni, bhante, raññaṃ khattiyānaṃ muddhāvasittānaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.7"
msgid "ajjhāvasantānaṃ assayuddhāni bhavanti … pe …"
msgstr "cavalry,"

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.8"
msgid "rathayuddhāni bhavanti … pe …"
msgstr "chariots,"

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.9"
msgid "pattiyuddhāni bhavanti;"
msgstr "or infantry."

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.10"
msgid ""
"tesampi, bhante, pattiyuddhānaṃ natthi gati natthi visayo adhivattamāne "
"jarāmaraṇe."
msgstr ""
"But there is no place, no scope for such battles when old age and death are "
"advancing."

#. VAR: pahonti → yesaṃ honti (mr)
msgctxt "sn3.25:4.11"
msgid ""
"Santi kho pana, bhante, imasmiṃ rājakule mantino mahāmattā, ye pahonti āgate "
"paccatthike mantehi bhedayituṃ."
msgstr ""
"In this royal court there are ministers of wise counsel who are capable of "
"dividing an approaching enemy by wise counsel."

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.12"
msgid ""
"Tesampi, bhante, mantayuddhānaṃ natthi gati natthi visayo adhivattamāne "
"jarāmaraṇe."
msgstr ""
"But there is no place, no scope for such diplomatic battles when old age and "
"death are advancing."

# bhumigata and vehasattha are stock in this phrase. they’re explained in Pj2 as “underground” (assuming that bhumigata and bhumatta are synonyms) and “above the ground”.
msgctxt "sn3.25:4.13"
msgid ""
"Saṃvijjati kho pana, bhante, imasmiṃ rājakule pahūtaṃ hiraññasuvaṇṇaṃ "
"bhūmigatañceva vehāsaṭṭhañca, yena mayaṃ pahoma āgate paccatthike dhanena "
"upalāpetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"In this royal court there is abundant gold coin and bullion stored in "
"dungeons and towers. Using this wealth we can pay off an approaching enemy."

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.14"
msgid ""
"Tesampi, bhante, dhanayuddhānaṃ natthi gati natthi visayo adhivattamāne "
"jarāmaraṇe."
msgstr ""
"But there is no place, no scope for such monetary battles when old age and "
"death are advancing."

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.15"
msgid ""
"Adhivattamāne ca me, bhante, jarāmaraṇe kimassa karaṇīyaṃ aññatra "
"dhammacariyāya samacariyāya kusalakiriyāya puññakiriyāyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"When old age and death are advancing, what can I do but practice the "
"teachings, practice morality, doing skillful and good actions?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.25:5.1"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, mahārāja, evametaṃ, mahārāja."
msgstr "“That’s so true, great king! That’s so true!"

msgctxt "sn3.25:5.2"
msgid ""
"Adhivattamāne jarāmaraṇe kimassa karaṇīyaṃ aññatra dhammacariyāya "
"samacariyāya kusalakiriyāya puññakiriyāyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"When old age and death are advancing, what can you do but practice the "
"teachings, practice morality, doing skillful and good actions?”"

msgctxt "sn3.25:5.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn3.25:5.4"
msgid "satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.25:6.1"
msgid "“Yathāpi selā vipulā,"
msgstr "“Suppose there were vast mountains"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:6.2"
msgid "nabhaṃ āhacca pabbatā;"
msgstr "of solid rock touching the sky"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:6.3"
msgid "Samantānupariyāyeyyuṃ,"
msgstr "drawing in from all sides"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:6.4"
msgid "nippothento catuddisā."
msgstr "and crushing the four quarters."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.25:7.1"
msgid "Evaṃ jarā ca maccu ca,"
msgstr "So too old age and death"

#. <br>
#. VAR: pāṇine → pāṇino (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn3.25:7.2"
msgid "adhivattanti pāṇine;"
msgstr "advance upon all living creatures—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:7.3"
msgid "Khattiye brāhmaṇe vesse,"
msgstr "aristocrats, brahmins, merchants,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:7.4"
msgid "sudde caṇḍālapukkuse;"
msgstr "workers, outcastes, and scavengers."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Na kiñci → na kañci (?)
msgctxt "sn3.25:7.5"
msgid "Na kiñci parivajjeti,"
msgstr "They spare nothing."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:7.6"
msgid "sabbamevābhimaddati."
msgstr "They crush all beneath them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.25:8.1"
msgid "Na tattha hatthīnaṃ bhūmi,"
msgstr "There’s nowhere for elephants to take a stand,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:8.2"
msgid "na rathānaṃ na pattiyā;"
msgstr "nor chariots nor infantry."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:8.3"
msgid "Na cāpi mantayuddhena,"
msgstr "They can’t be defeated"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:8.4"
msgid "sakkā jetuṃ dhanena vā."
msgstr "by diplomatic battles or by wealth."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.229"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.25:9.1"
msgid "Tasmā hi paṇḍito poso,"
msgstr "That’s why an astute person,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:9.2"
msgid "sampassaṃ atthamattano;"
msgstr "seeing what’s good for themselves,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:9.3"
msgid "Buddhe dhamme ca saṅghe ca,"
msgstr "being wise, would place faith"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:9.4"
msgid "dhīro saddhaṃ nivesaye."
msgstr "in the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
#. VAR: dhammaṃ cari → dhammacārī (bj, s1-3, km, pts1) | dhammacāri (pts2)
msgctxt "sn3.25:10.1"
msgid "Yo dhammaṃ cari kāyena,"
msgstr "Whoever lives by the teaching"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:10.2"
msgid "vācāya uda cetasā;"
msgstr "in body, speech, and mind,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:10.3"
msgid "Idheva naṃ pasaṃsanti,"
msgstr "is praised in this life"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:10.4"
msgid "pecca sagge pamodatī”ti."
msgstr "and departs to rejoice in heaven.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn3.25:10.5"
msgid "Tatiyo vaggo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.25:11.1"
msgid "Puggalo ayyikā loko,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
#. VAR: issattaṃ → issatthaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts2)
msgctxt "sn3.25:11.2"
msgid "issattaṃ pabbatūpamā;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:11.3"
msgid "Desitaṃ buddhaseṭṭhena,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:11.4"
msgid "imaṃ kosalapañcakanti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn3.25:11.5"
msgid "Kosalasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ."
msgstr "The Linked Discourses with the Kosalan are completed."
